Necropsy often shows the liver to be enlarged and discolored, with multifocal yellowish white lesions of varying size (Fig. 10.2
). Exudate in the biliary tree is common, along with dilatation of bile ducts. Microscopically, papillomatous hyperplasia of the ducts along with multiple life-cycle stages of the organism can be observed in the biliary epithelium (Fig. 10.3
).
